hydra-rag-hooks (0.1.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial release.
  * Successor to claude-rag-hook (v0.6.x). Same keyword-triggered
    UserPromptSubmit hook design, now extended to support BOTH Claude
    Code and OpenAI's Codex CLI from a single package. The two hooks
    share state: same on-disk index, same embedder cache, same
    toggles.json (so flipping auto-rag mode on flips it for both
    CLIs), same MCP server.
  * Unified family layout. Per-user state lives at
    ~/.config/hydra-llm/rag-hooks/, ~/.cache/hydra-llm/rag-hooks/,
    ~/.local/state/hydra-llm/rag-hooks/. Existing
    ~/.config/claude-rag-hook/ trees are migrated in place on first
    invocation. The model cache is shared across the hydra-* family
    at /var/cache/hydra-llm/models/ (with one-shot copy from the
    legacy /var/cache/claude-rag-hook/models/ if present).
  * Index folder renamed from .claude-rag-index/ to .hydra-index/.
    Existing folders are auto-renamed in place on first hook run;
    embeddings and chunks survive the rename byte-for-byte. The new
    name matches what hydra-llm has always used, so all three tools
    now share one index folder by default. The legacy name is still
    read transparently for one or two minor versions before being
    removed.
  * New: Codex CLI hook (UserPromptSubmit). Codex's envelope shape
    differs from Claude Code's, so we ship a separate adapter at
    bin/hydra-rag-hooks-codex-hook that wraps the same retrieval and
    indexing pipeline. Codex install is per-user opt-in via
    `codex plugin add /usr/lib/hydra-rag-hooks/codex-plugin` (Codex
    has no managed-settings system-wide install path; this is the
    documented way).
  * Inherits from claude-rag-hook v0.6.1: bundled MCP server,
    auto-rag toggle, /rag-toggle slash command, crh export/import
    for sharing indexes, retrieval safety on daemon-spawn failure,
    safety guards on ~/.claude.json and user-owned slash command
    files, path-traversal-safe import. See the v0.6.0 and v0.6.1
    sections of the claude-rag-hook changelog for the original
    features. Recommended migration path: apt remove claude-rag-hook
    after `apt install hydra-rag-hooks` (or wait for the
    claude-rag-hook v0.7.0 transitional shim that auto-pulls this
    package).

